  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The simulation pipeline is built on a commercial finite-volume CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2) coupled to a custom Python post-processing module that computes the relative hemolysis index via Lagrangian particle tracking. All validation runs completed nominally; a single documented solver restart due to a mesh-quality warning at the inlet shroud was resolved by reducing the under-relaxation factor and is considered fully mitigated.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
