      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-01-mesh-convergence",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence study — nominal completion",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study (coarse 2.1M, medium 5.4M, fine 12.8M cells) performed on the FDA pump geometry at 2.5 L/min, 3500 RPM. GCI-based discretization error for RH index: 3.2%. All three runs completed without solver interruption. Residuals converged to 1e-5 for continuity and momentum. No numerical exceptions or NaN values reported in solver logs."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-02-piv-velocity",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "PIV velocity field comparison — nominal completion",
      "description": "Simulated velocity magnitude distributions compared against FDA PIV benchmark data at three axial planes. Mean absolute error 6.8%, within the 10% acceptance threshold. Simulation completed nominally across all five flow-speed operating points. Solver logs indicate clean exit status for all cases; no convergence failures or floating-point overflow events were encountered."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-03-hemolysis-rh",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index validation — nominal completion",
      "description": "Computed RH index compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements from three independent laboratories. RH < 1 for all five operating conditions; mean RH = 0.74 (±0.09). Lagrangian particle tracking post-processing module executed without exception across all 5 cases and 12 geometric variants. All Python post-processing scripts returned exit code 0. A single solver restart was required at the inlet shroud due to a mesh-quality warning; after reducing the under-relaxation factor the case completed nominally and the restart event is documented as fully resolved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-04-sensitivity",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Geometric tolerance sensitivity sweep — nominal completion",
      "description": "Parametric sweep across 12 geometric variants (±tolerance bands on impeller tip clearance, volute width, inlet diameter) executed via ANSYS Fluent journal automation. All 12 cases completed without solver abort. RH sensitivity to tip clearance identified as dominant: ΔRHI = 0.18 per 0.1 mm change. No edge-case operating points were tested beyond the five nominal flow-speed combinations specified in the COU; all runs reported nominal completion with converged residuals."
    }
