      "rationale": "All production and validation runs converged to continuity and momentum residuals below 1e-5. Global mass imbalance < 0.005% in all cases. A single case required a restart after a mesh-quality warning at the inlet shroud; after adjustment of under-relaxation factors, the case converged nominally and the event is documented as resolved. Numerical solver error is assessed as within acceptable bounds at MRL 2. It is noted that iterative convergence was verified only under the five nominal operating conditions; solver behavior under off-design conditions approaching stall or surge was not evaluated, and no testing was performed to characterize solver response to degenerate inputs such as zero-flow initialization or extreme pressure boundary transients."
